' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
'  Notes
' ─────────────────────────────────────────────
note top of BaseSandboxSession
  **Template Method pattern**
  start() orchestrates: _ensure_backend_started →
  _prepare_backend_workspace → _ensure_runtime_helpers →
  _start_workspace → _after_start.
  Subclasses override individual hook methods.
  stop() persists snapshot only;
  shutdown() tears down the backend.
  aclose() = pre_stop_hooks → stop → shutdown.
end note

note right of SandboxSession
  **Decorator / Instrumentation wrapper**
  Every operation is wrapped with _annotate()
  which emits SandboxSession{Start,Finish}Event
  audit events and optional SDK trace spans.
  Callers always receive SandboxSession —
  _inner holds the real backend session.
end note

note bottom of SandboxSessionState
  **Discriminated-union registry**
  parse() dispatches to the correct registered
  subclass using the 'type' field.
  Every subclass auto-registers itself via
  __pydantic_init_subclass__ with its
  Literal 'type' default.
end note

note bottom of UnixLocalSandboxSession
  **macOS confinement**: exec commands are
  wrapped with sandbox-exec using an SBPL
  profile that denies broad host filesystem reads.
  Refuses manifest users/groups to avoid
  affecting the host OS.
end note

note bottom of DockerSandboxSession
  **Docker exec backend**
  Workspace persistence = copy_archive (tar stream).
  Reconnects to existing container on resume.
  Supports PTY sessions and volume mounts.
  Both backends track PTY processes in
  _pty_processes dict with LRU-style pruning.
end note

@enduml
